<h1>LDAP access</h1>
<table>
  <tr>
    <td>Hostname/Port (via TLS)</td>
    <td>{{ aedir_main_provider_hostname }}:636</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Search base</td>
    <td>{{ aedir_suffix }}</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>LDAP URL</td>
    <td><code>ldaps://{{ aedir_main_provider_hostname }}/{{ aedir_suffix }}</code></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p>
  Use with OpenLDAP command-line tools (with standard CA cert bundle for
  validating the server cert issued by
  <a href="https://letsencrypt.org/">Letâ€™s Encrypt</a>):
</p>

<pre>
$ LDAPTLS_CACERT=/etc/ssl/ca-bundle.pem ldapwhoami -H ldaps://{{ aedir_main_provider_hostname }} -x -D "uid=zots,{{ aedir_suffix }}" -w CorrectHorseBatteryStaple
